description: Probably from a Queensland Aboriginal language.

entries.meaning: Acacia catenulata, a species of acacia tree endemic to some arid areas in Queensland and the Northern Territory, Australia. [from 19th c.]
examples: On the flank of the rise the African buffel grass gave way to bare patches of red gravel between thin strands of sandalwood and bendee, spiky tussocks of purple wiregrass and buck spinifex.
